entry.sense:
katanN 
for kat-aAnN: 
see an ex. in a verse cited voce XaAribN.

laA walaA karaAmapF No; nor a jar-cover: i. e., No: (I will not give thee, or I will not do, what thou requirest,) nor anything else. 
See Hub-N; 
and see takorimap.

takorimapN 
syn. with takoriymN; (Mgh;) subst. from kar-amotuhu; 
as also karaAmapN↓. (Mṣb.)

5. takar-ahahu 
He showed, or expressed, dislike, disapprobation, or hatred, of it; 
see taOaj-amahu 
and tasax-aTahu: 
and takaAraha↓ Ealyohi signifies the same; 
see qanaHa.

kariyhN 
Disliked, disapproved of, blamed, or hated; hateful, blameable, displeasing, or odious; 
as also makoruwhN↓.

kal-ati AlOayodiI The hands, or arms, became weak; 
syn. DEft [i. e. DaEufato]. (Ḥam, 296.) 
[kal-a Eano fiEolK He was fatigued, or weak, and so disabled, or incapacitated, from doing a thing; 
like OaEoyaA Eanohu, and DaEufa Eanohu: 
see nuxiba 
and Earisa.]

Also, and mukan-FI↓, accord. to De Sacy, in his Ar. Gr. i. 455, 
or mukan-K↓, for I find its plural written in a copy of the Ṣ mukan-iyaAt, A pronoun; 
see kanaI.

kuw-apN and kaw-apN (Ṣ, Mṣb, Ḳ) and kaw-N (Ḳ) A hole, or perforation. or an aperture, (Ṣ, Mgh, Mṣb, Ḳ,) in a wall (Mṣb, Ḳ) or chamber; 
(Ṣ, Mgh;) [a mural aperture;] or the first and second, a small one; and the third, a large one (Ḳ.) 
See also miXokaApN.
